Internet domains are set up in accordance with the Domain Name Service (DNS), an application layer protocol and service used on networks to translate host names to their associated IP addresses. DNS is an essential component of the internet. It is implemented as a decentralized, heirachial system that's distributed globally across a conglomeration of DNS servers. The service acts as a giant directory foe resolving domain names to IP addresses and IP addresses to domain names, irrespective of where both domain are located.0